    "experience": {
      "title": "Experience",
      "columns": 1,
      "hidden": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "id": "jdhvmuj5hqy6kvexai3htxbp",
          "hidden": false,
          "company": "AWS Data Center Systems",
          "position": "Sr. SDE",
          "location": "Denver, CO",
          "period": "April 2024 - Present",
          "website": {
            "url": "",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p><strong>Telemetry Collection in Amazon Dedicated Cloud</strong></p><ul><li><p>Led the deployment of a telemetry polling service in 25 new data centers across North America. This service collects building management system (BMS) data via Modbus and BACnet protocols in order to optimize energy usage for data center cooling and server placement. Partnered with 5 teams in other organizations to get new networks setup, VMs configured, and deployments scheduled. Defined the ownership strategy and RACI model for how the teams would work in unison to deliver the project over the course of 10 months. Led the security review process to achieve signoff of the updated design and implementation via the AWS AppSec process.</p></li><li><p>Required: Technical Leadership, Modbus, BACnet, Python, Virtual Machines, Application Security, Cloud Architecture, On-Premise Design</p></li></ul><p><strong>High-Resolution Power Measurement System (Project Phasor)</strong></p><ul><li><p>Led Project Phasor as technical lead for three-engineer team, delivering $6MM annual power optimization savings through high-resolution data center monitoring. Engineered data collection system to achieve 3,000Hz sampling rate and designed cloud architecture to handle 150TB daily throughput for planned expansion to 50+ AI and ML data centers. Pioneered team's first Docker container deployment framework and developed cloud-based load testing methodology for lab infrastructure validation. Drove 12-month production implementation from single-facility prototype to 12 data center deployment. Authored technical specifications and presented architectural design and business impact to 450-person organization at company all-hands.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Cloud Scada Operational Dashboards</strong></p><ul><li><p>Created and led development of Cloud SCADA Operations Dashboard framework using CDK and CloudWatch, enabling multi-team collaboration across AWS data center operations. Established dashboard architecture adopted by 10 engineers across 6 teams, becoming critical operational tool for weekly leadership and org-wide ops reviews. Designed reusable components reducing dashboard development time from weeks to days. Dashboard provides real-time operational metrics across distributed systems allowing us to discover trends (throughput, latency, availability) that were previously unknown.</p></li></ul>",
          "roles": []
        },
        {
          "id": "e6hna2kth0oklrk07gl33y0f",
          "hidden": false,
          "company": "AWS Supply Chain",
          "position": "SDE II",
          "location": "Denver, CO",
          "period": "August 2022 - April 2024",
          "website": {
            "url": "",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p><strong>N-Tier Collaboration Routing Service:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Led a team of 13 engineers to develop a backend REST API to handle CSV file upload and download of interactions between AWS Supply Chain customers and their trading partners. Created high level design/architecture of the new service, including code structure and CI/CD pipeline structure. Delegated sub-component design to 4 other engineers across 14 design artifacts. Consisted of 14 API endpoints developed over 4 months, resulting in 35,000 new lines of source code and 5 new CI/CD pipelines. Deployed the new service at the \"General Availability\"  AWS launch bar, the highest deployment bar available for AWS launches.</p></li><li><p>Required: Kotlin, AWS Fargate, AuthN, AuthZ, CI/CD, AWS CloudWatch, AWS DynamoDB, AWS ALB, Technical Leadership, System Architecture</p></li></ul><p><strong>Supply Chain Product Location Service:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Designed and developed a backend REST API to handle management of product locations within customer owned fulfillment facilities. Led high-level design of the Location service - a new backend microservice, delegated low level designs to 5 engineers for aspects of the system. Led a team of 10 developers to contribute code to the service and deliver on an aggressive 5 month timeline. Worked with the product team to simplify and reduce product requirements for an optimal MVP while still delivering a delightful UX.</p></li><li><p>Required: Kotlin, AWS Fargate, AWS ALB, CI/CD, AWS DynamoDB, Data Modeling + Access Pattern Analysis, System Design, Team Leadership, CDK, CloudFormation</p></li></ul><p><strong>AWS Application Security Guardian:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Joined the AWS AppSec Guardian program - a volunteer program for security-minded SDEs who help lead teams through AWS AppSec certification prior to new product launch. Led the Guardian program in the Supply Chain organization, became the lead Guardian in an org of 250 engineers. Helped more than 10 software teams get AppSec certified on time - resulting in successful launch of multiple Supply Chain modules.</p></li><li><p>Required: Technical Leadership, Operational Improvement, Process Improvement, Force Multiplication, Security Expertise, Cryptography, Authentication, Authorization</p></li></ul><p><strong>EDI ML Auto Association:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Designed and developed a backend REST API to handle mapping of customer EDI messages against a Canonical Data Model (CDM) by leveraging Natural Language Processing (NLP) ML. Designed &amp; developed the backend system to deploy the ML model developed by research scientists into production. Launched the Auto Association service at re:Invent conference. Delegated work across 6 developers to deliver service on the launch date.</p></li><li><p>Required: Kotlin, AWS Fargate, AWS ALB, CI/CD, AWS DynamoDB, AWS SageMaker, AWS SageMaker Notebooks, Data Modeling + Access Pattern Analysis</p></li></ul><p></p>",
          "roles": []
        },
        {
          "id": "vrl6u4rr4mtxlpgs2xlqdv88",
          "hidden": false,
          "company": "AWS Data Center Systems",
          "position": "SDE II",
          "location": "Denver, CO",
          "period": "July 2020 - August 2022",
          "website": {
            "url": "",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p><strong>On-Prem Device Provisioning Service:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Designed and developed a global hardware provisioning system in AWS. Namely responsible for design of the backend provisioning system API and persistence of inventory. Service is scaled to provision 500k + devices across 100+ Data Centers.</p></li><li><p>Required: Python3, AWS Lambda, AWS DynamoDB, Data Modeling + Access Pattern Analysis</p></li></ul>",
          "roles": []
        },
        {
          "id": "uwzyd6tf26m22zs4r0vrx9r3",
          "hidden": false,
          "company": "AWS Data Center Systems",
          "position": "SDE I",
          "location": "Denver, CO",
          "period": "September 2018 - July 2020",
          "website": {
            "url": "",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p><strong>Document Sharing Security Audit Service:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Designed and developed an AWS service that scans tens of thousands of user accounts and millions of documents in AWS WorkDocs for security vulnerabilities daily. Reduced document bloat by 12 TB and saved the org more than $1MM in AWS WorkDocs costs annually. Detected hundreds of security risks and mitigated them with the DocEye service.</p></li><li><p>Required: Java, AWS Lambda, AWS CloudWatch, OOP, TDD, Integration Testing</p></li></ul><p><strong>Firewall Centralized Log Monitoring:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Designed and developed a centralized log monitoring service in AWS that analyzed log messages from thousands of firewalls globally in near real-time. Detected and alarmed on hundreds of security events (malformed firewall rules, incorrect configs, etc.).</p></li><li><p>Required: Java, AWS Lambda, AWS CloudWatch, OOP, Distributed Systems, Data Streaming</p></li></ul>",
          "roles": []
        },
        {
          "id": "l62940h6aei2kxau7lubgvmv",
          "hidden": false,
          "company": "AWS Data Center Systems",
          "position": "SDE Intern",
          "location": "Broomfield, CO",
          "period": "June 2017 - August 2017",
          "website": {
            "url": "",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p><strong>Remote Server Administration Service:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Worked within the Data Center Systems organization to build a web service that allowed secure rebooting (Auth N + Z) of critical servers in the datacenter. Previously to reboot these servers a data center technician needed to manually reboot via SSH, after the launch of RebootUI hundreds of hours have been saved by allowing secure remote reboot.</p></li><li><p>Required: Java, SpringBoot, OOP, RESTful API Design, HTML, CSS</p></li></ul>",
          "roles": []
        },
        {
          "id": "h9daq0n9p02g1b71avz363dt",
          "hidden": false,
          "company": "Micron Technology",
          "position": "Software Engineering Intern",
          "location": "Longmont, CO",
          "period": "January 2017 - May 2017",
          "website": {
            "url": "",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p><strong>JIRA CLI Tool:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Worked with the Engineering Services team to automate creation/maintenance of objects in JIRA and Confluence via RESTful APIs. Vended an internal CLI tool to help with management of JIRA and Confluence for engineering teams.</p></li><li><p>Required: Python, Java, JIRA, Confluence, Git, and Pylint</p></li></ul>",
          "roles": []
        }
      ]
