          "name": "Happy Hour Finder",
          "period": "2019 - Present",
          "website": {
            "url": "https://www.hottesthappyhours.com/",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p>Designed and implemented a new webapp to crowdsource the best happy hours based on a user's location. This service runs in AWS using API Gateway and AWS Lambda (Serverless). For data storage it leverages AWS DynamoDB and uses the Uber H3 geohashing framework to allow for geographic searching. The frontend is built using React and is deployed using AWS Amplify. It supports auto-completion of addresses using the Google Maps API.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": "vgdjmxzljccis9m6lkppgzo1",
          "hidden": false,
          "name": "Map-based Art Generator",
          "period": "2022-2023",
          "website": {
            "url": "http://mapart-website-s3-dev-us-west-2-263839118990.s3-website-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/",
            "label": ""
          },
          "description": "<p>Designed and implemented a new service that uses an open-source map generation python library to vend images of unique map art. This service is hosted on AWS Lambda with API-gateway. It uses up to 10 GB of memory for large maps, and it required altering the underlying map library to run in a Docker container on AWS Lambda. Maps are saved into S3, and all past maps can be viewed historically.</p>"
        }
